!!! 5
%html
  %head
    = Haml::Engine.new(File.read('_header.haml')).render(Object.new, :title => 'Mathias Soeken')
    %link(href="css/lstools.css" rel="stylesheet")
  %body
    .container#main-container
      .row#main-row
        = Haml::Engine.new(File.read('_nav.haml')).render(Object.new, :page => 'index')
        .col-md-9
          .starter-template
            %img#nav-picture(src="images/nav-picture2.jpg" align="right")
            %h1 Dr. Mathias Soeken
            %p.lead Researcher, Lausanne, Switzerland
          .row
            .col-md-8
              %p(style="text-align: justify")
                Mathias Soeken works as a research design engineer at
                %b Microsoft
                and as a researcher at the
                %b
                  %a(href="http://lsi.epfl.ch" target="_blank") EPFL
                in Lausanne, Switzerland.
                From 2009 to 2015 he worked at the
                %b University of Bremen, Germany
                and has been a regularly visiting post doc at
                %b UC Berkeley, CA, USA
                in the group of Robert K. Brayton.
                He holds a Ph.D. degree (Dr.-Ing.) in Computer Science from University of Bremen, Germany (2013).
                His research interests are logic synthesis, quantum computing, reversible logic, and formal verification.
                Mathias Soeken is member of the IEEE and of the ACM.
              #box
                %a(href="https://github.com/msoeken/alice" target="_blank")
                  %img#alice(src="https://cdn.rawgit.com/msoeken/alice/master/alice.svg")
                %a(href="https://github.com/hriener/easy" target="_blank")
                  %img#easy(src="https://cdn.rawgit.com/hriener/easy/master/easy.svg")
